The paper deals with algorithms for graph matching and sampling, which are fundamental topics in computer science. The use of peeling algorithms and recursive sampling processes suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-categories. The focus on approximation algorithms and constant factor approximations suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of space efficiency and local computation algorithms suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
